access: The Cabana is a stand alone structure located on the back of the property steps from the waters edge.  Access to shared yard, shared pool, shared dock. Bedroom Queen bed and pullout queen sized couch are for  those who may have difficulty with the head clearance in loft.

access: For the ease of our guests, we place your keys in a lockbox hanging on the doorknob outside of your unit.  Simply enter the code found below from the center of the lock and then press the separate silver key DOWN towards the ground, and not in towards the door.  Your room key will be inside.  Please do NOT remove the lockbox from the doorknob.  Please do NOT disturb the black security tape on the inside of the lockbox. At the end of your stay, please do return the key into the lockbox, or place it on the kitchenette table in clear view. For security reasons, these codes can be updated from time to time. If you've any questions at all, feel free to contact us straight away.  Mahalo.

name: Apt in Lapa, Rio's bohemian cradle
access: The apartment access to the world famous "Rio scenarium", the "Carioca da Gema", the "Lapa 40", the "Bar Brazil", the "Mangue Seco", the "New Chapel" among other places to eat, drink, listen to live music and dance, is done on foot. The famous "Old River Fair" or "Fair Lavradio" as it is popularly known by locals, which takes place every first Saturday of each month from 10am to 19h, is 5 minutes walk from the apartment.  The neighborhood of Lapa is integrated with bus lines and subway allowing easy access to the famous beaches of Copacabana, Ipanema and Leblon. The traditional sights - Sugar Loaf, Christ the Redeemer, Lagoa Rodrigo de Freitas, Sambadrome, Maracanã, Botanical Garden - are also easily accessed. access: North Shore, Oahu If there is such a thing as a perfect wave, you’ll likely find it on Oahu’s North Shore. The big, glassy winter waves of this legendary surf mecca attract the best surfers in the world, while summer waves are far smaller and more gentle – all of which makes the North Shore the perfect surf spot for beginners and veterans alike. Stretching for more than 7 miles, the beaches of the North Shore host the world’s premier surfing competitions during the peak, winter months, including the Super Bowl of wave riding, the Vans Triple Crown of Surfing (November - December). Stroll in the thick sands of Waimea Bay, Ehukai Beach (Banzai Pipeline) and Sunset Beach — just leave the surfing to the pros. The months between November and February are the best times to watch big wave surfing. The complex provides shuffleboard and volleyball courts, a pool, a children’s wading pool, hot tub, a putting green, gas barbecues and even a sauna. Each well-appointed unit includes its very own private lanai (balcony). The complex also has coin-operated laundry facilities on property for your convenience. Kauhale Makai’s location on South Kihei Road makes it the perfect base for exploring this magical island. Just minutes away are some of the world’s most beautiful beaches, superb shopping, renowned restaurants, and world-class golf.
